text: Faridunovka () is a rural locality (a village) in Sergiopolsky Selsoviet, Davlekanovsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 134 as of 2010. There are 2 streets. == Geography == It is located 4 km from Davlekanovo, 15 km from Sergiopol. == References == Category:Rural localities in Davlekanovsky District
title: Faridunovka
